packageMeta.name: purescript-maps

modules.name: Data.Map
modules.comments:
This module defines a type of maps as balanced 2-3 trees, based on
<http://www.cs.princeton.edu/~dpw/courses/cos326-12/ass/2-3-trees.pdf>

declarations.comments: `Map k v` represents maps from keys of type `k` to values of type `v`.

declarations.comments:
Check whether the underlying tree satisfies the 2-3 invariant

This function is provided for internal use.

modules.name: Data.StrMap
modules.comments:
This module defines a type of native Javascript maps which
require the keys to be strings.

To maximize performance, Javascript objects are not wrapped,
and some native code is used even when it's not necessary.

declarations.comments: `StrMap a` represents a map from `String`s to values of type `a`.
declarations.title: StrMap

declarations.comments: Convert a mutable map into an immutable map
declarations.title: freezeST

declarations.comments:
Freeze a mutable map, creating an immutable map. Use this function as you would use
`Prelude.runST` to freeze a mutable reference.

The rank-2 type prevents the map from escaping the scope of `runST`.
declarations.title: runST

modules.name: Data.StrMap.ST
modules.comments:
Helper functions for working with mutable maps using the `ST` effect.

This module can be used when performance is important and mutation is a local effect.

declarations.comments:
A reference to a mutable map

The first type parameter represents the memory region which the map belongs to. The second type parameter defines the type of elements of the mutable array.

The runtime representation of a value of type `STStrMap h a` is the same as that of `StrMap a`, except that mutation is allowed.
declarations.title: STStrMap

declarations.comments: Create a new, empty mutable map
declarations.title: new

declarations.comments: Get the value for a key in a mutable map
declarations.title: peek

declarations.comments: Update the value for a key in a mutable map
declarations.title: poke

declarations.comments: Remove a key and the corresponding value from a mutable map
declarations.title: delete

declarations.comments:
Unsafely get the map out of ST without copying it

If you later change the ST version of the map the pure value will also change.
declarations.title: unsafeFreeze

declarations.comments:
Unsafely get the value for a key in a map.

This function does not check whether the key exists in the map.
declarations.title: unsafeIndex
